The first example doesn't work!!! The textbox for progress don't updated with the percentage value! I created a new blank aspx webforms and put on it two controls.

The aspx header with the async attribute:  
<%@ Page Language="C#" AutoEventWireup="true" CodeBehind="WebForm1.aspx.cs" Inherits="WebApplication1.WebForm1" Async="true" %>

The two controls:  
 <asp:textbox runat="server" id="textBox1"></asp:textbox>  
 <asp:button runat="server" id="StartProcessingButton" onclick="StartProcessingButton_Click" text="Process"/>

The CodeBehind:  
 public async void StartProcessingButton_Click(object sender, EventArgs e)  
 {  
 var progress = new Progress<int>(percent =>  
 {  
 textBox1.Text = percent + "%";  
 });

 await Task.Run(() => DoProcessing(progress));  
 textBox1.Text = "Done!";  
 }

 public void DoProcessing(IProgress<int> progress)  
 {  
 for (int i = 0; i != 10; ++i)  
 {  
 Thread.Sleep(1000);  
 if (progress != null)  
 progress.Report(i);  
 }  
 }

Any ideas???? Why don't work?? It's really simple example... I'm using .net framework 4.6.1
